---
/* WhyFails.astro — Updated messaging */
---

<section class="bg-white text-slate-900 py-20 lg:py-28 border-t border-slate-200">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-5xl">

    <!-- Section header -->
    <div class="mb-14 text-center lg:text-left">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-semibold mb-4">
        Why most business websites quietly fail
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto lg:mx-0">
        Not because businesses don’t invest — but because hidden technical and
        structural risks go unnoticed before scaling traffic.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Core reasons -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-10">
      
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-medium text-lg mb-2">
          Slow performance increases ad costs
        </h3>
        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
          A slow website doesn’t just lose visitors — it lowers Google Quality Score
          and Meta relevance, making every click more expensive.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="font-medium text-lg mb-2">
          Broken or missing tracking
        </h3>
        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
          Without reliable conversion tracking, marketing decisions become guesses,
          budgets get wasted, and scale becomes risky.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="font-medium text-lg mb-2">
          Structure that can’t scale
        </h3>
        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
          Many websites work today but require full rebuilds when adding booking,
          CRM, or new service pages.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="font-medium text-lg mb-2">
          No real ownership
        </h3>
        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
          If you don’t control hosting, domain, and code, your website is an
          operational dependency — not a business asset.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Closing line -->
    <div class="mt-16 border-t border-slate-200 pt-8">
      <p class="text-slate-700 max-w-3xl">
        The Website Due Diligence Audit reveals these risks — before they cost you growth.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
